  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your<strong> broccoli</strong> into florets, then add to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, put the tray[s] in the oven for 10-12 min or until tender, golden and crisp</p><p>Tip: Roasting the broccoli will help to remove excess moisture before adding to your sauce!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1677604466818-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1677604466818-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1677604466818-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1677604466818-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1677604466818-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into large bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632759173670-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632759173670-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632759173670-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632759173670-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632759173670-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel, then dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and dice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 15g <span class=\"text-purple\">[25g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g]</span> <strong>butter </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>and <strong>diced carrot </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632759177932-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632759177932-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632759177932-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632759177932-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632759177932-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic </strong>and dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>Dijon mustard </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the vegetables have softened, add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you’ll use the rest later!) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 30 secs, then add the <strong>vegetable stock </strong>and <strong>soft cheese</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>creamy sauce</strong></p>",
