    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the creamy sauce is thickening, drain your <strong>sweetcorn</strong></p><p>Return the <strong>drained potatoes </strong>to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a small splash of <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and mash until smooth</p><p>Add the <strong>drained sweetcorn</strong> and <strong>roasted broccoli</strong> to the creamy sauce with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>creamy pie filling</strong></p>",
